In our Telekom broadband project, common production issues include missing or incomplete CSV files, Self-hosted Integration Runtime outages, SQL Server connectivity problems, Copy Activity timeouts, source schema changes, incorrect parameters, overlapping pipeline runs, watermark errors, child-pipeline dependency issues and audit update failures.
Whenever an issue occurs, we first check ADF Monitor and collect the pipeline Run ID, failed activity, input, output, error details, rows read, rows copied, queue duration, Batch ID and business date. We then classify whether the problem belongs to ADF, the source system, SHIR infrastructure, network or data quality.
We avoid rerunning the complete pipeline without checking partial data. For example, if Copy Activity succeeds but only the audit update fails, we rerun only the audit step. If the CSV is missing, support coordinates with the source/backend team. If SHIR is overloaded, we reduce concurrency and scale the IR. We use batch-specific paths, control tables, stage-level statuses, row-count reconciliation and targeted restarts to prevent duplicate or missing data.
